.TH "pci_cfg_access_lock" 9 "pci_cfg_access_lock" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_cfg_access_lock \- Lock PCI config reads/writes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" pci_cfg_access_lock
.BI "(struct pci_dev *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
pci device struct
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
When access is locked, any userspace reads or writes to config
space and concurrent lock requests will sleep until access is
allowed via \fBpci_cfg_access_unlock\fP again.
